emitism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAntisemitismus. 4aDemokratiegeschichte. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4aPaulskirche. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAnti-Semitism.  aFrankfurt Parliament.  aHistory of democracy.  aNational Socialism.1 aAbsmeier, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalling, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrajer, Sven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGramlich, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöllnitz, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeerdmann, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirschmüller, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJungcurt, Uta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKröger, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLange, Nils, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLazarus, Rosemarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiebold, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Frank Lorenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReitzenstein, Julien, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobionek, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRojek, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenberger, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc